About me

 Early on, I started programming in Python when I was first entering Grade 5, and was immediately hooked when I found out what I could make in Pygame. Since then, i've made kernels, text editors, terminal libraries, networking libraries, games, and much more. Me and my brother Andrew(@ajmd17) have also participated in a few code jams, including making an interpreted language(and a few examples in it!) named Peach, and an online game about fighting off shitcoins.


 Currently, me and my brother are building Hyperion Game Engine using only modern techniques, and wrote the renderer completely from scratch for Vulkan. With a custom scripting language and multi-threaded rendering, our game engine gives solid performance while also being a great learning tool. I am currently rewriting parts of the language to allow for Just-In-Time(JIT) compilation.


 When it comes to programming, I take massive pride in my work. I make sure that what has to be done is done properly, and I will research a project to death. Even for this website I looked for the perfect frontent library to suit my needs, even though it would be something that is not familiar to me. For this site, I used TailwindCSS, and React for building simple and interactive interfaces. Even though I had not used either before, I always want to try new things to improve my knowledge of computer science as a whole. Whether it be a JIT compiler, a game engine, low level assembly for a bootloader, a kernel, or a website, it is always an absolute blast to work on something I love

); } export default About;
